        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Siloam, or near East Bend, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elkin...
Fairview...
Jonesville...
Boonville...
East Bend...
King...
and Nebo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
